# Lexical flip cards — “Definition” face

## Front of the card

- **Show only** an **English paraphrase / sense** (or exam-style **hint in English**).
- **Do not** put on the front:
  - the **target phrase** / exact collocation the learner must recall;
  - **Russian** (or any L2 gloss) on the **definition** side — learners may mentally translate the English paraphrase, then **flip** to check.
- In data, store paraphrase in a dedicated field (e.g. `paraphrase` or `flipDef`) and keep Russian in a field shown **only on the back** (e.g. `glossRu`).

## Back of the card

- **Target phrase** (exact chunk from the text or official key) + **line from the script** (or gap context).
- Optional **short Russian gloss** for self-check (`glossRu`), rendered below the line / speaker when present.

## Word Bank vs flip

- Word Bank can still show `paraphrase + em dash + Russian` in a **single hint** column for study/revision.
- The flip UI uses `u9FlipFrontDefFromItem` / `flipDef` so the **face** of the card stays English-only for guessing.

## Reference

- `index.html` — `u9FlipFrontDefFromItem`, `u9FlipRender`, `u9FlipPoolForDeck`, `screen-unit9-lex-flip`.
- Track 10 Minds eye pack: `js/minds-eye-listen-data.js` — `U9_MINDS_EYE_WB_LEAD` with `paraphrase`, `glossRu`, `phrase`.
